Rating: 3
I doubled this recipe and used skinless chicken. We didn't miss the extra fat! Because I pounded the breasts pretty thin, the chicken was very tender and flavorful. You cannot skip that step! I used very good balsamic vinegar flavored with tangerine which sounds weird but was delicious. I skipped adding the fresh lemon juice because of that. All four of my kids, aged 7-17 loved it and the whole dinner including vegetable, salad and tri-colored pasta came together in exactly 30 minutes - crucial for crazy weeknights. We'll do this one again!

